Everlasting Moments;;84;;90;;NC;;In Sweden in the early 1900s, "Everlasting Moments" chronicles the life of Maria Lawson (Maria Heiskanen), an immigrant from Finland who uses a camera she wins in a lottery to document her life. Maria works with her camera to support her children while tolerating frequent abuse from Sigfrid (Mikael Persbrandt), her womanizing and alcoholic husband. Maria's daughter Maja, who vividly presents her mother's strength and dignity in the face of considerable hardship, narrates the film.;;Drama;;Jan Troell;;2009;;Maria Heiskanen,Mikael Persbrandt,Jesper Christensen,Emil Jensen,Ghita NÃ¸rby,Amanda Ooms,Antti Reini,Birte Heribertsson,Claire Wikholm;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/everlasting_moments